Tree Canopy Assessment
In 2013, City Council approved spending up to $10,000 from the Tree Trust Fund to engage an arborist for surveying the City’s tree canopy.
Climate Mitigation and Adaptation Task Force
In December of 2015 City Council authorized the formation of the Climate Mitigation and Adaptation Task Force, in 2016 Task Force Members were appointed and in 2017 the Task Force began meeting.

The initial goals of the Task Force included, advance adaptation and mitigation strategies to enhance resilience and preparedness for withstanding the effects of climate change; promoting education, incentives and public outreach and the generation of suggestions in obtaining grants and other financial resources to offset program costs.  After a series of meetings, these goals were expanded and explored in more detail.

The Task Force was comprised of subject matter experts from a broad variety of experience and expertise.

In November of 2018 the Task Force issued its final report to include recommendations for success.

Parks & Recreation Board
Parks & Recreation Surveys
The City of Pensacola Parks and Recreation department would like your feedback to help us improve services and facilities for you and your community. We encourage you to fill out the surveys and share this link with others so we can reach more community members. Your input is greatly appreciated and will help shape the future of the City of Pensacola Parks and Recreation.
Sponsorships
SPONSORSHIP OPPORTUNITIES
Be part of our winning team! We have a variety of opportunities for local businesses or community organizations to support our efforts in the following program areas:

Special Events (Senior Games, Annual Easter Easter Egg Hunt, Mayor’s Cup, Trunk or Treat)
Parks (Playground Equipment, Tables, Benches, Shelters)
Youth and Athletic Programs (Uniforms, Equipment, Teams)
Summer Camp (T-shirts, Field Trips, Registration)
Swimming Lessons
Parks make a community more attractive and the recreational activities provide a better way of life. They play an important role in shaping the lives of our youth, senior citizens, and families. You can help be becoming a sponsor and showing your support for your community today.

Activity Guide
Check out the City of Pensacola Parks and Recreation Activity Guide, The Playbook!
Summer Camps
The Pensacola Parks and Recreation Department offers summer camps and specialty camps to keep the kids active and entertained all summer long. Find out more about camps at the location nearest you and register today!
Athletics & Sports
Explore the City's various athletics programs.
Adult Sports
Learn more about the adult sport events offered by the City such as Flag Football, Kickball, Softball and the Pensacola Seniors Games.
Youth Sports
Athletic Facilities
Recreational Basketball League
Youth Coaching and Mentoring through athletics and academics offered in inner-city resource centers.
Dance Classes
Dance classes are offered in a variety of disciplines for youth and adults. We offer dance lessons in ballet, tap, jazz, pointe, hip-hop, lyrical, modern, Irish, belly dance, line dancing, tumbling and more. 

Gull Point Resource Center is the place to be in Pensacola for dance instruction and is home to the Gull Point Performing Dancers.  

Dance classes are offered in a variety of disciplines for youth and adults. We offer ballet, tap, jazz, pointe, hip-hop, lyrical, modern, Irish, belly dance, line dancing, tumbling and more.
Events Calendar
A full listing of upcoming events.
Movies In the Park Series
Hill-Kelly Drive In Movie Series
After School Program
Outdoor Pursuits Adventure Programs
Get ready to explore nature, learn new skills, and have a lot of fun in Play Pensacola Parks and Recreation's Outdoor Pursuits Adventure Programs. We offer a wide variety of outdoor adventures ranging from summer camps and one day skills clinics in archery, camping, fishing, and paddle sports to wilderness survival training and everything in between.
Outdoor Pursuits Youth Adventures
Outdoor Pursuits Youth Camps for kids 8-16
Outdoor Pursuits Adult (16+) Programs
Outdoor excursions for adults and teens 16+
Outdoor Pursuits Rentals
The Penacola Parks and Recreation Outdoor Pursuits Center offers affordable rentals for Kayaks, Grills, Backpacking equipment, bicycles, standup paddleboards, and more.
Pensacola Senior Games
The City of Pensacola Parks and Recreation Department and Humana are proud to present the 2017 Pensacola Senior Games September 8-24. Athletes age 50 and older can compete in 21 sporting events including bocce, horse shoes, bowling, darts, track and field, tennis, swimming, and more. Whether this is your first year to compete or you are a seasoned athlete, we are sure you’ll find an event just for you!
Special Event Permitting
It is required by ordinance that application for a special event in the City of Pensacola be made at least 10 days prior to the desired date of the event.
Volunteer
Give a gift - volunteer with the Parks and Recreation Department today.
Yoga in the Park
Free Yoga in the Park
Bayview Senior Performing Arts Series
Held September through May, Bayview Senior Center partners with performing artists to bring engaging artistic entertainment to the older adult community.
